=== Economic Burden
<subsec:economic>

*Pre-COVID Estimates.*
The National Academy of Medicine (2015) estimated annual U.S.\ economic burden at \$17–24 billion. Updated analyses accounting for population growth and inflation revised this to \$36–51 billion annually @Jason2020economic.

*Post-COVID Estimates.*
With ME/CFS prevalence potentially increasing from 1.5 million to 5–9 million U.S.\ cases due to post-COVID onset, updated economic impact estimates range from \$149–362 billion annually @Jason2022prevalence. This includes direct medical costs and lost productivity but excludes disability benefits, social services, and caregiver lost wages, suggesting the true economic burden is substantially higher.
